settings.name: RandomizeDreamers
settings.description: Allow for Dreamers to be randomized into the item pool and opens their locations for randomization.

settings.name: RandomizeSkills
settings.description: Allow for Skills, such as Mantis Claw or Shade Soul, to be randomized into the item pool. Also opens their locations for receiving randomized items.

settings.name: RandomizeFocus
settings.description: Disabled Option. Not implemented.

settings.name: RandomizeSwim
settings.description: Disabled Option. Not implemented.

settings.name: RandomizeCharms
settings.description: Allow for Charms to be randomized into the item pool and open their locations for randomization. Includes Charms sold in shops.

settings.name: RandomizeKeys
settings.description: Allow for Keys to be randomized into the item pool. Includes those sold in shops.

settings.name: RandomizeMaskShards
settings.description: Allow for Mask Shard to be randomized into the item pool and open their locations for randomization.

settings.name: RandomizeVesselFragments
settings.description: Allow for Vessel Fragments to be randomized into the item pool and open their locations for randomization.

settings.name: RandomizeCharmNotches
settings.description: Allow for Charm Notches to be randomized into the item pool. Includes those sold by Salubra.

settings.name: RandomizePaleOre
settings.description: Randomize Pale Ores into the item pool and open their locations for randomization.

settings.name: RandomizeGeoChests
settings.description: Allow for Geo Chests to contain randomized items, as well as their Geo reward being randomized into the item pool.

settings.name: RandomizeJunkPitChests
settings.description: Randomize the contents of junk pit chests into the item pool and open their locations for randomization.

settings.name: RandomizeRancidEggs
settings.description: Randomize Rancid Eggs into the item pool and open their locations for randomization.

settings.name: RandomizeRelics
settings.description: Randomize Relics (King's Idol, et al.) into the item pool and open their locations for randomization.

settings.name: RandomizeWhisperingRoots
settings.description: Randomize the essence rewards from Whispering Roots into the item pool. Whispering Roots will now grant a randomized item when completed. This can be previewed by standing on the root.

settings.name: RandomizeBossEssence
settings.description: Randomize boss essence drops, such as those for defeating Warrior Dreams, into the item pool and open their locations for randomization.

settings.name: RandomizeGrubs
settings.description: Randomize Grubs into the item pool and open their locations for randomization.

settings.name: RandomizeMimics
settings.description: Disabled Option. Not implemented.

settings.name: RandomizeMaps
settings.description: Randomize Maps into the item pool. This causes Cornifer to give you a message allowing you to see and buy an item that is randomized into that location as well.

settings.name: RandomizeStags
settings.description: Randomize Stag Stations unlocks into the item pool as well as placing randomized items on the stag station bell/toll.

settings.name: RandomizeLifebloodCocoons
settings.description: Randomize Lifeblood Cocoon grants into the item pool and open their locations for randomization.

settings.name: RandomizeGrimmkinFlames
settings.description: Randomize Grimmkin Flames into the item pool and open their locations for randomization.

settings.name: RandomizeJournalEntries
settings.description: Randomize the Hunter's Journal as well as the findable journal entries into the item pool, and open their locations for randomization. Does not include journal entries gained by killing enemies.

settings.name: RandomizeNail
settings.description: Disabled Option. Not implemented.

settings.name: RandomizeGeoRocks
settings.description: Randomize Geo Rock rewards into the item pool and open their locations for randomization.

settings.name: RandomizeBossGeo
settings.description: Randomize boss Geo drops into the item pool and open those locations for randomization.

settings.name: RandomizeSoulTotems
settings.description: Randomize Soul Refill items into the item pool and open the Soul Totem locations for randomization.

settings.name: RandomizeLoreTablets
settings.description: Randomize Lore items into the itempool, one per Lore Tablet, and place randomized item grants on the tablets themselves. You must still read the tablet to get the item.

settings.name: PreciseMovement
settings.description: Places skips into logic which require extremely precise player movement, possibly without movement skills such as dash or hook.

settings.name: ProficientCombat
settings.description: Places skips into logic which require proficient combat, possibly with limited items.

settings.name: BackgroundObjectPogos
settings.description: Places skips into logic for locations which are reachable via pogoing off of background objects.

settings.name: EnemyPogos
settings.description: Places skips into logic for locations which are reachable via pogos off of enemies.

settings.name: ObscureSkips
settings.description: Places skips into logic which are considered obscure enough that a beginner is not expected to know them.

settings.name: ShadeSkips
settings.description: Places shade skips into logic which utilize the player's shade for pogoing or damage boosting.

settings.name: InfectionSkips
settings.description: Places skips into logic which are only possible after the crossroads become infected.

settings.name: FireballSkips
settings.description: Places skips into logic which require the use of spells to reset fall speed while in mid-air.

settings.name: SpikeTunnels
settings.description: Places skips into logic which require the navigation of narrow tunnels filled with spikes.

settings.name: AcidSkips
settings.description: Places skips into logic which require crossing a pool of acid without Isma's Tear, or water if swim is disabled.

settings.name: DamageBoosts
settings.description: Places skips into logic which require you to take damage from an enemy or hazard to progress.

settings.name: DangerousSkips
settings.description: Places skips into logic which contain a high risk of taking damage.

settings.name: DarkRooms
settings.description: Places skips into logic which require navigating dark rooms without the use of the Lumafly Lantern.

settings.name: ComplexSkips
settings.description: Places skips into logic which require intense setup or are obscure even beyond advanced skip standards.

settings.name: DifficultSkips
settings.description: Places skips into logic which are considered more difficult than typical.

settings.name: RemoveSpellUpgrades
settings.description: Removes the second level of all spells from the item pool.

settings.name: StartLocation
settings.description: Choose your start location.

settings.name: MinimumGrubPrice
settings.description: The minimum grub price in the range of prices that an item should cost from Grubfather.

settings.name: MaximumGrubPrice
settings.description: The maximum grub price in the range of prices that an item should cost from Grubfather.

settings.name: MinimumEssencePrice
settings.description: The minimum essence price in the range of prices that an item should cost from Seer.

settings.name: MaximumEssencePrice
settings.description: The maximum essence price in the range of prices that an item should cost from Seer.

settings.name: MinimumCharmPrice
settings.description: The minimum charm price in the range of prices that an item should cost for Salubra's shop item which also carry a charm cost.

settings.name: MaximumCharmPrice
settings.description: The minimum charm price in the range of prices that an item should cost for Salubra's shop item which also carry a charm cost.

settings.name: RandomCharmCosts
settings.description: Total Notch Cost of all Charms together. Set to -1 for vanilla costs, or to -2 to shuffle the vanilla costs. Vanilla sums to 90. This value is distributed among all charms in a random fashion.

settings.name: MinimumEggPrice
settings.description: The minimum rancid egg price in the range of prices that an item should cost from Ijii. Only takes effect if the EggSlotShops option is greater than 0.

settings.name: MaximumEggPrice
settings.description: The minimum rancid egg price in the range of prices that an item should cost from Ijii. Only takes effect if the EggSlotShops option is greater than 0.

settings.name: EggShopSlots
settings.description: For each slot, add a location to the Egg Shop and a Geo drop to the item pool.

settings.name: Goal
settings.description: Determines which goal will send a victory condition to the AP server.

settings.name: WhitePalace
settings.description: Whether or not to include White Palace or not. *Note*: Even if excluded, the King Fragment check may still be required if charms are vanilla.

settings.name: StartingGeo
settings.description: The amount of Geo you start with.
